def find_variables_to_remove(corr_mat, x):
    corr_mat = corr_mat.stack().reset_index()
    corr_mat.columns = ['variable_1', 'variable_2', 'Correlation']
    corr_mat = corr_mat.loc[corr_mat['variable_1'] != corr_mat['variable_2'], :]
    corr_mat['Correlation_abs'] = np.abs(corr_mat['Correlation'])
    corr_mat = corr_mat.sort_values('Correlation_abs', ascending=False)
    corr_mat = corr_mat[corr_mat['Correlation_abs']>=x]
    
    variables_to_remove = []
    seen_variables = []
    correlated_pairs = []
    
    for _, row in corr_mat.iterrows():
        var1 = row['variable_1']
        var2 = row['variable_2']
        tupla = (var1, var2)
        tupla_inv = (var2, var1)

        if (tupla not in seen_variables) and (tupla_inv not in seen_variables):
            variables_to_remove.append(tupla)
            seen_variables.append(tupla)

            correlated_pairs.append((var1, var2, row['Correlation'], row['Correlation_abs']))
    
    correlated_df = pd.DataFrame(correlated_pairs, columns=['Variable 1', 'Variable 2', 'Correlation', 'Correlation_abs'])
    
    return variables_to_remove, correlated_df
    #return corr_mat
